      • configure

        public BuiltUpload configure(JSONObject jsonObject)
        Creates new instance of BuiltUpload from valid org.json.JSONObject. If JSON object is not appropriate then it will return null.
        Parameters:
        jsonObject - json object of particular file attached in the built object.
        BuiltUpload can be generate using of data filled BuiltObject and #configure(org.json.JSONObject).


        Example :

        1. Single Attachment :-
            //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
    BuiltApplication builtApplication = Built.application(context,"blt5d4sample2633b");

    BuiltUpload uploadObject = builtApplication.upload();
        
    uploadObject.configure(builtObject.getJSONObject(attached_image_field_uid));

        2. Multiple Attachment :-
        
    JSONArray array = builtObject.getJSONArray(Attach_Image_Field_Uid);
        
    for (int i = 0; i < array.length(); i++) {
        
          BuiltUpload uploadObject = builtApplication.upload();
        
          uploadObject.configure(builtObject.getJSONObject(attached_image_field_uid));
        
    }
        Returns:
        BuiltUpload instance.

      • on

        public void on(Built.EventType eventType,
      com.raweng.built.BuiltOnEventCallback callback)
        This function registers an event listener.

        [Only avaliable with realtime]
        Parameters:
        eventType - event name.
        callback - BuiltOnEventCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Given below is the list of supported events.

        Create[Work with BuiltApplication.upload()] :- Create event is triggered when a new file is uploaded in this application. Registered callback is invoked with the uploaded data.

        Update :- Update event is triggered when the content and/or the ACL of a BuiltUpload on this application is modified. Registered callback is invoked with the updated upload data.

        Delete :- Delete event is triggered when a BuiltUpload on this application is deleted. Registered callback is invoked with the deleted upload data.

        Broadcast :- Broadcast event is triggered when a message is broadcast over this BuiltUpload instance. Registered callback is invoked with the broadcast message.



        Example 
         // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 BuiltApplication builtApplication  = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b");
 BuiltUpload uploadObject = builtApplication.upload();
 //for example we are using EventType.CREATE.
 uploadObject.on(Built.EventType.CREATE, new BuiltOnEventCallback() {

      @Override
      public void onReceive(Object object, BuiltError error) {

      }
 });
